    • Method Detail

      • getMessage

        Message getMessage()
        The message payload will always contain the common fields:
        • Resource.getId()
        • Resource.getVersion()
        • Message.getSequenceNumber()
        • Message.getResourceVersion()
        • Resource.getCreatedAt()
        • Resource.getLastModifiedAt()
        for any message. If the payload fits within the size limit of you message queue (the limit is often 256kb), all additional fields for the specific message are included as well (along with the Message.getType() property). If the payload did not fit, it can be retrieved from the Messages endpoint if messages are enabled.

        You can check if this payloads contains a complete message with hasCompleteMessage(). In this case you can use as(Class) to retrieve the typed message.

        Returns:
        the message payload
